Key Match Events: India won by 10 wickets (with 28 balls remaining)
Yashasvi Jaiswal and Shubman Gill made light work of a 153-run target
Wessly Madhevere and Tadiwanashe Marumani added 63 in 8.4 overs
Abhishek Sharma claimed his first international wicket with the dismissal of Sikandar Raza
Post-Match Reflections: India had plenty to cheer about in Harare
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zimbabwe's most-assured batting effort wasn't enough to mount a challenge against India's young IPL stars
India's fifth-bowlers shine after Zimbabwe's solid foundation
